Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them 
onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and 
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop two thirds of the @garlic cloves{3}(unpeeled) into a small piece 
of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it. Peel and grate the 
rest.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @tomato ketchup{1%portioned}, 
@salt for the burgers{1/4%tsp}, @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and grated garlic, 
then add the @British beef mince{240%g}. Season with pepper and mix together 
with your hands.

Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 
per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto another #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of 
your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

At the same time, roast the garlic parcel in the oven until soft, 
~{10-12%minutes}.

While the burgers cook, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the garlic has roasted and cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze 
it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

Pop the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, roasted garlic and @mayonnaise{64%g} into another 
#large bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix well to combine. Taste 
and season again if needed.

Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}.

Once cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers and pop back 
into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, add the burger buns to the tray to warm through, 
~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, top each bun base with a cheesy burger and the bun lid.

Serve with the wedges and slaw alongside.

Enjoy!